Micronaut reports error if a path variable is declared the URL path and the corresponding parameter is missing in a method signature. The quick-fix adds the missing parameter.
```
  @Get("/path/{variable}/")
  public String handle(String name_not_equal_to_variable) {
    ...
  }
```

This PR bundles various updates to the CSS/LESS support in  NetBeans, as many changes depend on changes to the lexer/parser and the generated code makes it unfeasible to separate them into different PRs.

Parsing support for @layer
------------------------------

```css
@layer module, utilities, state;
@import "utils.css" layer(utilities);


@layer state {
    /** */
}

@layer module {
  /** */
}
```

Enhanced `@supports` support
---------------------------------

@supports constructs which involved function-style checks added to the supported set.

```css
@supports selector(h2 > p) {
}

@supports font-tech(color-COLRv1) {
}

@supports font-format(opentype) {
}
```

Support for the CSS containment module was added
----------------------------------------------------------

```css
.post {
  container-type: inline-size;
  container-name: sidebar;
}

@container sidebar (min-width: 400px) {
  /* <stylesheet> */
}
```

Properties of CSS text module level 4 were mapped
---------------------------------------------------------

```css
.hints {
    hyphenate-character: auto;
    hyphenate-limit-chars: 10;
}
```

Math functions (min, max, clamp, ...) are now recognized by the property parser
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```css
.hints {
    font-size: min(25px, 2rem);
    margin: 0px 0px min(5px, 0.26cqh);
    margin-top: max(2px, 10%);
}
```

The `optional` keyword for LESS imports is now recognized
-----------------------------------------------------------------

```less
@import (optional) "user.less";
```

